{
  "stem": "26111.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And across the entire door and the entire-- of course, the-- the-- the sign itself and the whole front of the house was splattered with this 'Jude' and various other slogans, 'Juden raus,' and, and all kinds of really nasty things.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I mean, this, this was-- I will never forget my father's face when he saw that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This must have been like a-- like a dagger in his-- in his heart.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he must have intellectually-- as I said, he was an exceptionally intelligent man-- he must have intellectually known something like that was coming.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was inevitable.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Even, even the most assimilated would be, at some point, hit with this.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "How far it would go, of course, nobody knew at that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But this was the first time it really came home to him!",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That was his sign, his name besmirched by these vermin.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'34 or '35, fairly shortly after the Nazis came to power in '33.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was at that time that he met-- I'll now go on to answer your question, why did we leave Konigsberg and went to Berlin?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At that time, he met a disciple of Karl Gustav Jung, the, the Swiss psychiatrist, and through him, met Jung himself.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he had been getting more and more interested in psychoanalysis and psychiatry.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And apparently, they-- this whole group made a big impression on each other.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was invited to, to join Jung's group as a-- not, not on a permanent basis, but to take part in certain courses and certain seminars, and so on.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the other gentleman who was-- had been a disciple of Jung.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he was a German Jew and had opened his practice, had had a psychoanalytic practice in Berlin for quite some time, a very brilliant one.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
